    • Method Detail

      • postPickContainerization

        org.w3c.dom.Document postPickContainerization(YFSEnvironment env,
                                              org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                                       throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                              java.rmi.RemoteException

        The postPickContainerization API is used to containerize and generate SCM labels for all shipment lines belonging to either a Shipment, Batch or Inventory Pallet. If the postPickContainerization API is invoked with ShipNode and either BatchNo or InventoryPalletId, then we will fetch all tasks that are part of the specified Batch or Inventory Pallet and containerize them. If The postPickContainerization API is invoked with either ShipmentKey or ShipmentNo,SellerOrganizationCode and ShipNode, we will containerize all shipment lines belonging to the specified shipment.

        The generation of SCM labels is driven by the Pack Constraints configuration. If SCM generation is configured to be system generated , then we will generate SCM labels either for only cases, or for cases and pallets based on the configuration.
